Description: Body sherd of Aeolian Wild Goat Style pottery dinos; white slip; interior: streaky black with possible traces of bands in added white and bands in added red; exterior: from top, frieze with cross and dotted chevrons and short dashed crosses as filling ornament; below, wide black band above frieze with grazing goat to right (added purple on neck and hindquarters; only hind legs missing); dashes, short zigzags, dashed cross, dot rosette, and large standing triangle an filling ornament; below, part of band.
Producer name: Attributed to: The London Dinos Group
Bibliographic references: Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p.242, no.1)
Kerschner 2006 / On the Provenance of Aiolian Pottery (p.122 fig.4, Appendix 2 Nau2)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GK.09)
